            "subject": "LU-458 debug: use profilenm before running class_del_profile()"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Yu Jian",
          "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-05-21 06:23:28.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Yu Jian",
          "email": "yujian@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2012-05-21 08:21:14.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-458 debug: print client profile name correctly",
        "message": "LU-458 debug: print client profile name correctly\n\nThis patch reverts commit 48c2f667236e2f41f9fd0224b5de7a83517b3180,\nwhich does not print client profile name correctly and introduces\na new defect that the client profile is not deleted properly.\n\nIn ll_put_super(), the memory space pointed to by profilenm is\nin fact freed inside lustre_common_put_super(sb), which is called\nbefore LCONSOLE_WARN(). In order to print the client profile name\nin LCONSOLE_WARN(), we need copy the contents of profilenm to a\ntemporary storage before freeing profilenm.\n\nSigned-off-by: Yu Jian <yujian@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I9ce2f304f3bad4761d2e3c857e4cdd5df6269c38\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
  },
